1
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:35,020
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,490 --> 00:01:37,940
[Episode 28]

3
00:01:42,259 --> 00:01:43,190
Take this money.

4
00:01:43,870 --> 00:01:44,930
If I don't finish the task,

5
00:01:44,930 --> 00:01:46,530
Shengli won't let me go back.

6
00:01:47,140 --> 00:01:48,100
Thank him for me.

7
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:49,009
Thank him yourself.

8
00:01:49,009 --> 00:01:50,610
Stop using me as a messenger.

9
00:01:50,650 --> 00:01:51,810
He's been very tired lately,

10
00:01:51,810 --> 00:01:54,670
traveling back and forth
between Russia and China.

11
00:01:55,140 --> 00:01:56,200
How is your mother?

12
00:01:56,780 --> 00:01:57,509
Much better.

13
00:01:57,539 --> 00:01:58,570
That's good.

14
00:01:58,570 --> 00:02:00,030
Heaven protects the good.

15
00:02:00,180 --> 00:02:00,950
How are you guys doing?

16
00:02:00,950 --> 00:02:02,410
Is everything going well?

17
00:02:02,850 --> 00:02:04,090
With Mr. Lucky around,

18
00:02:04,090 --> 00:02:06,330
any accident will turn out fine.

19
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:09,030
Did something happen?

20
00:02:10,900 --> 00:02:11,400
See?

21
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:13,030
I told you any accident
would turn out fine.

22
00:02:13,030 --> 00:02:14,430
Why are you still asking?

23
00:02:14,430 --> 00:02:15,580
You are worried about him, aren't you?

24
00:02:15,580 --> 00:02:16,230
It's fine. It's fine.

25
00:02:16,230 --> 00:02:17,329
Everything's great.

26
00:02:17,329 --> 00:02:18,210
Don't just sit there.

27
00:02:18,210 --> 00:02:19,470
Have a bowl of noodles.

28
00:02:19,620 --> 00:02:20,750
I've already eaten.

29
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:26,930
It looks like

30
00:02:26,930 --> 00:02:28,730
you guys have made quite a scene.

31
00:02:29,079 --> 00:02:31,210
Does he still have time for that movie?

32
00:02:36,180 --> 00:02:37,180
Wh-What's wrong?

33
00:02:38,250 --> 00:02:39,650
I knew he didn't tell you.

34
00:02:42,130 --> 00:02:43,660
Is the movie not going well?

35
00:02:43,910 --> 00:02:45,090
Ask him yourself.

36
00:02:45,180 --> 00:02:46,020
If I tell you,

37
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:46,640
I'll...

38
00:02:46,780 --> 00:02:48,360
I'll be gossiping again.

39
00:02:52,860 --> 00:02:53,770
But if I tell you,

40
00:02:53,770 --> 00:02:55,170
don't say I told you that.

41
00:02:55,750 --> 00:02:57,000
It's not about
whether it's going well or not.

42
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,650
That movie fell through long ago.

43
00:02:58,650 --> 00:02:59,940
When did this happen?

44
00:03:00,060 --> 00:03:01,430
Right at the start of autumn.

45
00:03:01,430 --> 00:03:02,430
Were you two

46
00:03:03,590 --> 00:03:05,090
having a little fight

47
00:03:05,090 --> 00:03:06,690
and not contacting each other
or something?

48
00:03:06,690 --> 00:03:08,460
And his movie at that time...

49
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:09,140
didn't...

50
00:03:09,340 --> 00:03:10,650
didn't get its investment back.

51
00:03:10,650 --> 00:03:11,470
Not only did he owe favors,

52
00:03:11,470 --> 00:03:12,930
he also got into deep debt.

53
00:03:14,090 --> 00:03:14,960
He's in debt?

54
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,130
How much does he owe?

55
00:03:16,370 --> 00:03:17,090
That... that...

56
00:03:17,090 --> 00:03:18,090
That's nothing you need to worry about.

57
00:03:18,090 --> 00:03:19,360
Once we close this deal,

58
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,420
he'll cover the deficit.

59
00:03:20,420 --> 00:03:21,150
It's fine.

60
00:03:23,250 --> 00:03:24,100
I told him

61
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:25,900
that the movie industry is tough.

62
00:03:25,900 --> 00:03:26,960
The audience nowadays

63
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:27,650
is less and less willing to

64
00:03:27,650 --> 00:03:28,560
go to the cinema.

65
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:30,650
Everyone watches TV series at home, right?

66
00:03:30,650 --> 00:03:31,210
But look,

67
00:03:33,079 --> 00:03:34,530
you actually like Shengli quite a bit.

68
00:03:34,530 --> 00:03:36,390
And Shengli likes you too, right?

69
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:37,320
I feel like...

70
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:38,800
maybe you two

71
00:03:38,820 --> 00:03:40,420
think of each other too much.

72
00:03:40,650 --> 00:03:41,710
Communicate more,

73
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:43,800
keep in touch, and make phone calls.

74
00:03:44,410 --> 00:03:46,190
Any difficulty will pass.

75
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:47,010
Right?

76
00:03:47,460 --> 00:03:49,280
Let me tell you something honestly.

77
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:51,490
Even if fate is full of hardships,

78
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:54,650
even if it takes strange
and winding turns,

79
00:03:55,030 --> 00:03:56,840
don't cry, don't feel bitter.

80
00:03:57,590 --> 00:03:58,360
Shengli

81
00:03:58,630 --> 00:04:00,690
will definitely be with you forever.

82
00:04:04,310 --> 00:04:04,880
Right?

83
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:11,000
Sir, the chili here

84
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:11,990
is a bit too spicy.

85
00:04:11,990 --> 00:04:12,990
Do you have water?

86
00:04:13,310 --> 00:04:14,310
Do you have water?

87
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,010
Yes, we do.

88
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:16,370
But that's boiling water.

89
00:04:16,370 --> 00:04:17,630
Boiling water is fine.

90
00:04:21,170 --> 00:04:23,850
[Seasons Change Hostel]

91
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:22,920
Dad.

92
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:23,450
What?

93
00:04:23,510 --> 00:04:25,870
Are you really going back
to our hometown with me?

94
00:04:25,870 --> 00:04:27,130
How long will you stay?

95
00:04:27,420 --> 00:04:28,830
What do you mean by that?

96
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:30,250
That's my home.

97
00:04:30,370 --> 00:04:32,170
How long do you think I'll stay?

98
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:33,670
Geez.

99
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:35,190
Does that mean you will stay with me

100
00:04:35,190 --> 00:04:36,520
and Mom every day?

101
00:04:36,810 --> 00:04:37,830
Of course.

102
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:41,060
All these years in Beijing,

103
00:04:41,130 --> 00:04:43,420
I've just been making money
for your mom's treatment.

104
00:04:43,420 --> 00:04:46,360
Now that she's cured,
we can reunite at home.

105
00:04:47,180 --> 00:04:48,590
We have to work together

106
00:04:48,620 --> 00:04:50,280
to teach your mom how to speak.

107
00:04:50,430 --> 00:04:51,100
I know.

108
00:04:51,540 --> 00:04:53,250
The way I learned to speak
when I was little

109
00:04:53,250 --> 00:04:54,450
is how I'll teach Mom.

110
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:55,710
That's right.

111
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:58,390
You're a big boy now.

112
00:04:58,420 --> 00:04:58,900
Right?

113
00:04:59,060 --> 00:05:00,900
You should teach your mom

114
00:05:00,930 --> 00:05:02,030
to speak the way

115
00:05:02,060 --> 00:05:03,190
you'd teach a child.

116
00:05:11,430 --> 00:05:11,920
Right.

117
00:05:11,930 --> 00:05:14,380
When the three of us are together,

118
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:15,830
we can be at ease.

119
00:05:16,250 --> 00:05:18,300
Try to speak as much as you can.

120
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,630
Don't use gestures.

121
00:05:19,660 --> 00:05:21,610
You have to practice speaking.

122
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:23,170
Practice speaking. Speak.

123
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:25,720
You have to be brave enough to speak.

124
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:27,130
Speak. Don't gesture.

125
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:27,770
Speak.

126
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:33,580
Don't gesture.

127
00:05:33,630 --> 00:05:34,370
Understood.

128
00:05:34,430 --> 00:05:35,750
Understood. Understood.

129
00:05:35,750 --> 00:05:37,520
We can be at ease.

130
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:39,159
We can be at ease now.

131
00:05:39,370 --> 00:05:39,860
Right.

132
00:05:40,220 --> 00:05:40,920
When are we going

133
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:42,200
to see Ranran?

134
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:43,210
When?

135
00:05:43,890 --> 00:05:44,680
Let's set...

136
00:05:45,740 --> 00:05:46,390
Ranran?

137
00:05:47,310 --> 00:05:47,860
Ranran.

138
00:05:47,950 --> 00:05:49,740
Why did you come back alone?

139
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:51,120
Where's Liangliang?

140
00:05:51,659 --> 00:05:53,790
Liangliang went to buy train tickets.

141
00:05:53,870 --> 00:05:55,400
We need to go back to Huzhou.

142
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:01,330
Ranran,

143
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:02,410
my mom is asking,

144
00:06:02,450 --> 00:06:03,610
"Why are you back?

145
00:06:03,930 --> 00:06:05,060
How's your health?"

146
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:08,410
I'm fine. I'm fine.

147
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:10,360
Liangliang told me

148
00:06:10,740 --> 00:06:11,570
that you guys

149
00:06:12,350 --> 00:06:14,720
are going back to your hometown
in the next couple of days.

150
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:16,320
I want to say goodbye to you.

151
00:06:16,570 --> 00:06:17,860
We're not in a rush.

152
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:20,010
We're leaving the day after tomorrow.

153
00:06:20,750 --> 00:06:22,680
After you go back to your hometown,

154
00:06:23,220 --> 00:06:24,250
if there are any difficulties,

155
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:24,910
you must...

156
00:06:25,010 --> 00:06:25,680
you must...

157
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:26,880
call me.

158
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:27,510
Okay.

159
00:06:29,070 --> 00:06:30,250
Xiaobao, you too.

160
00:06:30,250 --> 00:06:31,150
You must study hard.

161
00:06:31,150 --> 00:06:32,550
You must learn more words

162
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:33,659
and write to me.

163
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:35,920
Don't worry, Ranran.

164
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,790
When my mother can speak,

165
00:06:37,890 --> 00:06:39,200
she will call you.

166
00:06:41,930 --> 00:06:42,909
Will it be...

167
00:06:43,890 --> 00:06:44,520
hard to

168
00:06:44,550 --> 00:06:46,080
see you again in the future?

169
00:06:46,420 --> 00:06:47,770
It's fine, Ranran.

170
00:06:48,220 --> 00:06:49,370
I... I...

171
00:06:49,370 --> 00:06:51,240
am going back to my hometown

172
00:06:51,260 --> 00:06:53,120
to work on making corn juice.

173
00:06:53,190 --> 00:06:54,580
The village will even pay

174
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:56,650
for me to come to Beijing

175
00:06:56,740 --> 00:06:58,390
to develop the market and study.

176
00:06:58,390 --> 00:06:59,340
When I come to Beijing again,

177
00:06:59,340 --> 00:07:01,670
I'll still stay at Seasons Change Hostel.

178
00:07:01,770 --> 00:07:03,340
I'll still stay in Room 108.

179
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,530
Don't worry.

180
00:07:04,740 --> 00:07:06,270
We'll see each other often.

181
00:07:08,130 --> 00:07:08,990
Ranran,

182
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:10,870
after I go back to my hometown,

183
00:07:10,870 --> 00:07:12,390
I won't be farming anymore.

184
00:07:12,390 --> 00:07:14,000
But in my heart,

185
00:07:14,450 --> 00:07:16,170
there is a new seed planted.

186
00:07:16,690 --> 00:07:18,490
Although leaving Beijing means

187
00:07:18,570 --> 00:07:20,270
fewer opportunities,

188
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:21,870
this seed in my heart

189
00:07:21,870 --> 00:07:23,590
can grow into crops

190
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:24,770
in my hometown

191
00:07:25,180 --> 00:07:26,530
and bring

192
00:07:26,810 --> 00:07:28,730
a new harvest.

193
00:07:29,740 --> 00:07:31,860
Be just like me,

194
00:07:32,110 --> 00:07:32,720
alright?

195
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:36,180
Mr. Guo,

196
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:37,120
Mrs. Guo.

197
00:07:38,630 --> 00:07:41,530
The next time you see me,

198
00:07:41,770 --> 00:07:43,090
I'll be a new Ranran.

199
00:07:43,570 --> 00:07:44,100
Alright.

200
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:55,060
Ranran,

201
00:07:55,310 --> 00:07:56,340
my mom said

202
00:07:56,830 --> 00:07:58,580
we would start over together.

203
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:00,810
As long as we have each other,

204
00:08:00,810 --> 00:08:02,600
tomorrow will be better.

205
00:08:05,620 --> 00:08:06,540
Ranran,

206
00:08:07,100 --> 00:08:08,500
you are our family.

207
00:08:13,310 --> 00:08:14,620
It's fine, Ranran.

208
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:18,610
We are family.

209
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:29,470
Meiqin,

210
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:32,080
this is what they call a turn of luck.

211
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,340
The shop hasn't been transferred yet,

212
00:08:34,340 --> 00:08:35,840
and you've already been discharged.

213
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:36,640
Are you happy?

214
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:38,010
Yes.

215
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:39,650
I am

216
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,720
just like this shop,

217
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:43,490
coming back to life.

218
00:08:44,290 --> 00:08:45,670
Why the rush?

219
00:08:45,770 --> 00:08:47,470
You just got discharged.

220
00:08:48,370 --> 00:08:50,170
I really can't stay idle at home.

221
00:08:50,510 --> 00:08:52,310
The customers are all regulars,

222
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:53,550
so they don't rush me.

223
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,340
Don't worry.

224
00:08:56,170 --> 00:08:58,170
I'll take it depending on my health.

225
00:09:01,370 --> 00:09:02,460
Then I'll

226
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:04,600
help my mom.

227
00:09:05,530 --> 00:09:06,410
No.

228
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:08,430
No one can take my shop from me,

229
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,400
not even my own daughter.

230
00:09:10,410 --> 00:09:12,000
Just hurry back to Beijing.

231
00:09:17,770 --> 00:09:19,150
These days,

232
00:09:19,550 --> 00:09:21,250
Shengli has helped us a lot.

233
00:09:22,290 --> 00:09:24,000
It's not easy for him to work hard

234
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:24,930
alone out there.

235
00:09:26,010 --> 00:09:27,600
And he doesn't have much money.

236
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,500
We need to

237
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:30,480
return this money to him.

238
00:09:31,670 --> 00:09:33,400
Where did this money come from?

239
00:09:33,550 --> 00:09:34,700
Mr. Yang's factory

240
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:36,010
is doing very well now.

241
00:09:36,270 --> 00:09:36,980
This is my

242
00:09:37,010 --> 00:09:38,630
agreed dividend.

243
00:09:41,770 --> 00:09:43,470
I can't take this money.

244
00:09:43,650 --> 00:09:45,050
I will pay it back myself.

245
00:09:45,130 --> 00:09:46,360
Listen to me.

246
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:48,130
I'm not asking about

247
00:09:48,170 --> 00:09:50,570
your relationship with Shengli right now.

248
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,070
But

249
00:09:52,870 --> 00:09:53,790
if you're going to

250
00:09:53,790 --> 00:09:55,160
keep things separate,

251
00:09:55,370 --> 00:09:57,430
return the money to him immediately.

252
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:03,400
If you're going to share everything...

253
00:10:04,410 --> 00:10:06,010
Then the money belongs to me.

254
00:10:06,030 --> 00:10:08,130
The money still has to go to Shengli.

255
00:10:08,460 --> 00:10:10,280
Do something together.

256
00:10:10,770 --> 00:10:12,510
As long as you have thought it through,

257
00:10:12,510 --> 00:10:13,430
just go for it.

258
00:10:13,870 --> 00:10:14,770
Your mom and I

259
00:10:15,010 --> 00:10:16,840
will always support you.

260
00:10:18,170 --> 00:10:19,320
The saying
"A friend in need is a friend indeed"

261
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,920
applies not just to friends,

262
00:10:21,670 --> 00:10:22,930
but to couples as well.

263
00:10:23,860 --> 00:10:26,090
Meeting someone who never leaves you

264
00:10:26,370 --> 00:10:28,100
and loves you wholeheartedly—

265
00:10:28,170 --> 00:10:29,460
that's a blessing,

266
00:10:29,790 --> 00:10:30,790
and luck.

267
00:10:31,890 --> 00:10:33,200
You should cherish it.

268
00:10:35,870 --> 00:10:36,510
Got it.

269
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,480
Are you going to pay up or not?

270
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:47,280
I don't have money. How can I pay?

271
00:10:55,010 --> 00:10:55,940
Stop beating me!

272
00:10:58,050 --> 00:10:59,770
Look at this!
This Chinese guy sold us fake goods!

273
00:10:59,770 --> 00:11:02,180
We're going to burn them!

274
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:05,670
We'll burn down your stall!

275
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:07,770
Stop beating me!

276
00:11:09,180 --> 00:11:10,740
Excuse me, excuse me!

277
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:11,680
Don't fight!

278
00:11:12,250 --> 00:11:13,120
Stop fighting!

279
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:16,360
Stop fighting!

280
00:11:16,410 --> 00:11:18,320
We know each other!

281
00:11:18,390 --> 00:11:19,550
Alright! Alright!

282
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:20,980
Don't fight.

283
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,250
-We know each other.
-What happened?

284
00:11:22,250 --> 00:11:23,050
Don't fight.

285
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:24,620
They bought a batch of shoes

286
00:11:24,620 --> 00:11:25,890
from me to resell.

287
00:11:26,030 --> 00:11:27,520
Some people bought them,
and they wore out quickly,

288
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:29,380
so they came back demanding I pay.

289
00:11:31,650 --> 00:11:32,130
Look.

290
00:11:32,890 --> 00:11:34,820
These shoes are all like this.

291
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:36,080
They didn't even last a week.

292
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:37,240
They're all garbage.

293
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:38,570
He has two choices now.

294
00:11:38,670 --> 00:11:40,500
First, pay up;

295
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:42,100
second, burn them all.

296
00:11:43,340 --> 00:11:44,670
Then pay for what you owe

297
00:11:44,750 --> 00:11:46,290
and exchange the goods for new ones.

298
00:11:46,290 --> 00:11:47,440
He wants me to pay 10 times.

299
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:48,820
How could I have that much money?

300
00:11:48,820 --> 00:11:49,340
I've already sent all my money

301
00:11:49,340 --> 00:11:50,450
to my wife and kid.

302
00:11:50,550 --> 00:11:51,670
I don't have cash here.

303
00:11:51,670 --> 00:11:52,270
If you knew it would be like this,

304
00:11:52,270 --> 00:11:53,370
why did you sell that junk?

305
00:11:53,370 --> 00:11:54,250
Don't mind him. It serves him right.

306
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:54,720
Let's go.

307
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:56,050
-I didn't know he would come to me.
-Let's go.

308
00:11:56,050 --> 00:11:56,830
Burn them.

309
00:11:57,010 --> 00:11:58,480
Everything you Chinese sell

310
00:11:58,480 --> 00:11:59,660
is garbage!

311
00:12:01,130 --> 00:12:02,060
What did you say?

312
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,210
Don't fight!

313
00:12:03,220 --> 00:12:05,010
We have goods.

314
00:12:05,220 --> 00:12:07,220
I have goods. I'll swap them for you.

315
00:12:07,390 --> 00:12:08,050
I'll do it.

316
00:12:08,910 --> 00:12:10,640
Chinese goods are all garbage.

317
00:12:10,770 --> 00:12:12,570
What are you going to trade with?

318
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:13,460
Our shoes

319
00:12:13,460 --> 00:12:14,430
are not like his.

320
00:12:14,910 --> 00:12:16,250
Then let me take a look.

321
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:19,510
You should have at least
discussed this with me.

322
00:12:19,510 --> 00:12:20,320
Seriously.

323
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:21,440
Our goods are good.

324
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:22,650
Come on, look.

325
00:12:27,940 --> 00:12:28,890
His shoes are so bad,

326
00:12:28,890 --> 00:12:30,010
even we wouldn't wear them.

327
00:12:30,010 --> 00:12:30,980
They don't represent Chinese goods.

328
00:12:30,980 --> 00:12:32,200
Our shoes are good.

329
00:12:32,550 --> 00:12:33,750
They can withstand pulling, dragging,

330
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:35,080
kicking, and stomping.

331
00:12:35,410 --> 00:12:37,510
This is real Chinese quality.

332
00:12:41,050 --> 00:12:41,780
How about it?

333
00:12:41,940 --> 00:12:42,510
Can we swap?

334
00:12:42,510 --> 00:12:43,480
Okay, we can.

335
00:12:43,540 --> 00:12:44,370
We need to check the goods.

336
00:12:44,370 --> 00:12:46,320
Just your three pairs?

337
00:12:46,970 --> 00:12:48,300
How many pairs in total?

338
00:12:49,510 --> 00:12:50,380
Fifty.

339
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:54,050
Look at the mess you got us into.

340
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:55,860
Well...

341
00:12:55,890 --> 00:12:57,080
I don't have 50 pairs here.

342
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:57,790
I have more in my car.

343
00:12:57,790 --> 00:12:58,640
Follow me.

344
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:00,720
You can go there and pick.

345
00:13:02,300 --> 00:13:04,620
Come with me.

346
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:05,730
Excuse me.

347
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:07,090
This way.

348
00:13:07,480 --> 00:13:09,560
Come on. Follow me.

349
00:13:10,550 --> 00:13:11,500
Do as you see fit.

350
00:13:11,630 --> 00:13:12,190
Sir...

351
00:13:12,620 --> 00:13:13,250
Thanks.

352
00:13:13,530 --> 00:13:14,100
Sir,

353
00:13:14,140 --> 00:13:16,870
I will definitely return
the money for the shoes.

354
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:19,330
I'm not helping you.

355
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:20,980
I'm doing it to maintain

356
00:13:20,980 --> 00:13:22,910
the reputation of Chinese people.

357
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:25,500
I know it's bad to sell fakes.

358
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:26,560
Right? I was wrong.

359
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:28,320
Your goods are of good quality,

360
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:29,520
but the profit is low.

361
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:31,010
How can we make money?

362
00:13:31,010 --> 00:13:32,610
When you do business abroad,

363
00:13:32,650 --> 00:13:34,250
you can't just think about money.

364
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:35,890
You represent the Chinese people.

365
00:13:35,890 --> 00:13:37,690
Don't lose face for the Chinese.

366
00:13:39,650 --> 00:13:40,890
Sir! Sir! Sir!

367
00:13:44,650 --> 00:13:45,200
Sir,

368
00:13:45,510 --> 00:13:47,040
do you still have the shoes?

369
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,560
I want to restock from you.

370
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:52,210
From today on,

371
00:13:52,510 --> 00:13:53,970
I will turn over a new leaf.

372
00:13:56,870 --> 00:13:57,290
Okay.

373
00:13:58,630 --> 00:13:59,650
Burn that batch

374
00:13:59,650 --> 00:14:01,120
of terrible shoes of yours first.

375
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:03,050
I'll burn them. I'll burn them all!

376
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:04,210
I'll do it right now!

377
00:14:04,550 --> 00:14:05,550
Thanks to Sophia,

378
00:14:06,130 --> 00:14:06,700
we were able

379
00:14:06,700 --> 00:14:08,360
to open up the Russian market.

380
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:09,650
But to be honest,

381
00:14:09,820 --> 00:14:10,890
I feel

382
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:11,870
a bit unfulfilled.

383
00:14:11,870 --> 00:14:13,580
Such a good product,

384
00:14:13,980 --> 00:14:15,050
yet we can't openly say

385
00:14:15,050 --> 00:14:16,310
they're made in China.

386
00:14:16,750 --> 00:14:17,340
We have to

387
00:14:17,340 --> 00:14:18,240
sell it abroad

388
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:19,650
in our Russian friend's name.

389
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:20,250
When will

390
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:21,130
everyone know

391
00:14:21,130 --> 00:14:22,030
our Chinese products

392
00:14:22,030 --> 00:14:23,230
are truly excellent?

393
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:25,620
This is great love.

394
00:14:26,050 --> 00:14:27,850
It's a long and arduous journey.

395
00:14:27,940 --> 00:14:29,000
But it's a good thing.

396
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,170
At least it taught those profiteers

397
00:14:30,170 --> 00:14:31,620
a lesson, right?

398
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:35,150
Sophia is back.

399
00:14:35,150 --> 00:14:36,210
Time to eat, right?

400
00:14:37,620 --> 00:14:38,670
Well...

401
00:14:41,340 --> 00:14:42,890
Should we bring out the hot dishes first?

402
00:14:42,890 --> 00:14:43,870
Please, this way.

403
00:14:43,870 --> 00:14:44,540
Okay, okay.

404
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:47,150
Jun, they are from
Wenzhou Hometown Association.

405
00:14:47,150 --> 00:14:48,080
Nice to meet you.

406
00:14:48,870 --> 00:14:49,700
Nice to meet you.

407
00:14:49,700 --> 00:14:50,070
Hello.

408
00:14:50,070 --> 00:14:51,320
-Hello.
-Hello. Hello.

409
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:52,820
We are representatives

410
00:14:52,860 --> 00:14:54,870
of the Wenzhou Hometown Association
in Russia.

411
00:14:54,870 --> 00:14:56,030
We heard you were here,

412
00:14:56,030 --> 00:14:57,170
so we hurried over to visit.

413
00:14:57,170 --> 00:14:57,700
Thank you.

414
00:14:57,700 --> 00:14:58,500
-Okay.
-Well…

415
00:14:59,290 --> 00:15:00,240
Did you come

416
00:15:00,250 --> 00:15:01,710
to visit us for something?

417
00:15:01,720 --> 00:15:03,720
Thanks to your being there that day,

418
00:15:04,630 --> 00:15:07,430
the reputation of Chinese businessmen
was saved.

419
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:09,620
So,

420
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,320
our Wenzhou Chamber of Commerce

421
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:13,320
made a pennant for you.

422
00:15:13,790 --> 00:15:15,720
This is a token of our respect.

423
00:15:16,290 --> 00:15:18,290
We hope you keep up the good work.

424
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:19,940
Please accept it.

425
00:15:23,150 --> 00:15:24,700
Here, accept it.

426
00:15:25,750 --> 00:15:27,430
This... This is

427
00:15:27,580 --> 00:15:29,130
an affirmation from our compatriots.

428
00:15:29,130 --> 00:15:30,220
This is an unexpected harvest.

429
00:15:30,220 --> 00:15:31,080
You deserve it.

430
00:15:31,290 --> 00:15:33,100
You are role models
for Chinese businessmen,

431
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:35,030
always putting credibility first

432
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:36,790
and giving priority to quality.

433
00:15:36,790 --> 00:15:37,590
-Yes.
-Right?

434
00:15:37,820 --> 00:15:38,960
Well...

435
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,670
Thank you for the affirmation.

436
00:15:40,670 --> 00:15:41,670
I will definitely

437
00:15:41,790 --> 00:15:42,860
hang it at home.

438
00:15:43,460 --> 00:15:44,770
Let's take a picture.

439
00:15:44,790 --> 00:15:45,670
Sure.

440
00:15:45,670 --> 00:15:46,170
Please.

441
00:15:46,190 --> 00:15:46,830
Please stand in the middle.

442
00:15:46,570 --> 00:15:50,300
[Outstanding Merchant—
Bringing Honor to the Nation]

443
00:15:49,010 --> 00:15:50,000
Get a little closer.

444
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:50,870
Okay.

445
00:15:50,870 --> 00:15:52,750
Okay, raise the pennant
a little higher on this side.

446
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:53,100
Okay.

447
00:15:53,580 --> 00:15:55,290
President, look at the camera.

448
00:15:55,290 --> 00:15:56,860
Three, two, one.

449
00:15:58,460 --> 00:15:59,240
Alright.

450
00:15:59,270 --> 00:16:00,340
Thank you.

451
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:04,580
You are the president
of Wenzhou Hometown Association?

452
00:16:04,580 --> 00:16:06,250
Our factory is also in Wenzhou.

453
00:16:06,250 --> 00:16:06,770
Right.

454
00:16:06,910 --> 00:16:08,530
President, what happened that day

455
00:16:08,530 --> 00:16:09,930
was just a coincidence.

456
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:12,000
Although the problem has been solved,

457
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:13,220
a pennant

458
00:16:13,250 --> 00:16:14,670
can't change the Russians'

459
00:16:14,670 --> 00:16:16,630
overall impression of Chinese goods.

460
00:16:16,630 --> 00:16:18,030
We are here doing business

461
00:16:18,030 --> 00:16:19,630
not just for a one-time deal.

462
00:16:19,660 --> 00:16:20,740
We want Russians,

463
00:16:20,760 --> 00:16:21,760
when they think of Chinese goods,

464
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:23,340
to think of them as reliable.

465
00:16:23,340 --> 00:16:25,980
We want them to say that Chinese products
are of high quality.

466
00:16:25,980 --> 00:16:26,960
Someone has to take the lead.

467
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:27,430
Yes.

468
00:16:27,650 --> 00:16:29,250
Someone has to take the lead.

469
00:16:29,510 --> 00:16:30,580
We know this.

470
00:16:30,790 --> 00:16:32,500
These fake and shoddy products

471
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:33,150
have made us

472
00:16:33,150 --> 00:16:34,550
legitimate businessmen

473
00:16:34,580 --> 00:16:35,840
suffer.

474
00:16:37,150 --> 00:16:38,010
How about this?

475
00:16:38,740 --> 00:16:39,980
Print a few more copies

476
00:16:39,980 --> 00:16:41,360
of the photo we just took for us.

477
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:42,600
We'll post them at home.

478
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:43,000
Right.

479
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:43,890
And in our factory.

480
00:16:43,890 --> 00:16:44,960
And let's make more

481
00:16:44,980 --> 00:16:45,920
of this pennant.

482
00:16:46,250 --> 00:16:46,970
Later,

483
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:48,220
you can take them back

484
00:16:48,220 --> 00:16:49,830
and hang them in front of the shops

485
00:16:49,830 --> 00:16:50,980
that sell genuine goods.

486
00:16:50,980 --> 00:16:52,720
Hang them wherever they are conspicuous.

487
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:53,870
First, this can serve as

488
00:16:53,870 --> 00:16:55,080
a reminder

489
00:16:55,170 --> 00:16:56,080
to those opportunists.

490
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:56,830
Second,

491
00:16:57,030 --> 00:16:57,790
it will give us—

492
00:16:57,790 --> 00:16:59,120
those who want to do legitimate business—

493
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:00,120
more confidence.

494
00:17:00,340 --> 00:17:01,030
Okay.

495
00:17:01,280 --> 00:17:03,310
Okay, I'll handle this.

496
00:17:05,810 --> 00:17:06,250
In the blink of an eye,

497
00:17:06,250 --> 00:17:08,069
Shengli is leaving tomorrow.

498
00:17:08,810 --> 00:17:10,270
I really hate to see him go.

499
00:17:10,829 --> 00:17:12,290
But there's nothing I can do.

500
00:17:12,290 --> 00:17:13,940
His sweetheart is far away,

501
00:17:13,940 --> 00:17:14,869
waiting for him.

502
00:17:19,050 --> 00:17:20,380
I want to say something.

503
00:17:23,750 --> 00:17:26,240
Thank you so much for bringing me along

504
00:17:26,260 --> 00:17:27,390
to do this business.

505
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:29,930
It made me very happy.

506
00:17:30,740 --> 00:17:32,810
Leave the business here to me.

507
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:34,320
I'll take good care of it.

508
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:35,680
I hope Shengli

509
00:17:35,830 --> 00:17:38,040
will visit my home often.

510
00:17:39,850 --> 00:17:40,380
Sophia.

511
00:17:41,810 --> 00:17:43,160
I look forward to your visit to Beijing.

512
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:43,960
We'll take you

513
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:45,420
to eat Beijing local food

514
00:17:45,900 --> 00:17:48,200
and to the Great Wall
and the Forbidden City.

515
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:48,690
Okay.

516
00:17:49,010 --> 00:17:51,140
Going to Beijing is my dream.

517
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:51,810
Cheers!

518
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:53,930
Come on, let's toast together.

519
00:17:53,940 --> 00:17:54,440
In China,

520
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:56,400
I'll take you wherever you want to go.

521
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:56,810
Okay.

522
00:18:01,790 --> 00:18:02,660
This business

523
00:18:03,690 --> 00:18:05,610
just somehow worked out.

524
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:08,020
No, I was confused.

525
00:18:08,420 --> 00:18:09,870
You had everything under control.

526
00:18:09,870 --> 00:18:11,220
What are you talking about?

527
00:18:11,220 --> 00:18:12,200
Jun, if you weren't here,

528
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:13,330
could I have done it?

529
00:18:15,880 --> 00:18:16,810
You can tell right away

530
00:18:16,810 --> 00:18:18,470
that you're good at business.

531
00:18:18,810 --> 00:18:19,500
Ordinary people

532
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:20,920
don't usually catch my eye.

533
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:21,790
But Shengli,

534
00:18:22,510 --> 00:18:23,070
after working together,

535
00:18:23,070 --> 00:18:24,420
I really admire you.

536
00:18:26,090 --> 00:18:27,910
So I'm not bad, huh?

537
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:29,570
Not bad. Very good.

538
00:18:33,880 --> 00:18:35,570
I was running back and forth recently

539
00:18:35,570 --> 00:18:37,880
and had no time to think about this.

540
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:39,680
Lately,

541
00:18:39,770 --> 00:18:41,400
things have stabilized a bit.

542
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:43,260
The debts are almost paid off too.

543
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:45,610
Actually, I've really thought about it.

544
00:18:45,610 --> 00:18:46,310
Maybe...

545
00:18:48,030 --> 00:18:49,760
this is really what I should do.

546
00:18:50,530 --> 00:18:52,140
Let's fix

547
00:18:52,140 --> 00:18:53,540
this model in the future.

548
00:18:53,640 --> 00:18:55,040
I'll be in charge of sales

549
00:18:55,070 --> 00:18:56,220
and business negotiations.

550
00:18:56,220 --> 00:18:58,000
Jun, you'll take charge of local matters.

551
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,770
And we can take those...

552
00:19:00,270 --> 00:19:01,230
Zhuang Zhuang.

553
00:19:02,070 --> 00:19:04,310
Production is our pillar.

554
00:19:04,810 --> 00:19:06,470
Zhuang Zhuang is your pillar.

555
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:09,330
Yes.

556
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:13,500
There was one time

557
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:14,700
when I came to Russia,

558
00:19:15,660 --> 00:19:17,510
my mom made a long-distance call,

559
00:19:17,510 --> 00:19:20,310
insisting that I go back
and eat zhajiang noodles.

560
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:22,030
I said, "You called from so far away

561
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:23,530
just to tell me
to go back for Zhajiang noodles?"

562
00:19:23,530 --> 00:19:25,130
I told her I was making money.

563
00:19:25,380 --> 00:19:26,510
My mom said, "You?

564
00:19:26,510 --> 00:19:27,910
Can you even make money?"

565
00:19:32,830 --> 00:19:33,760
Later I realized

566
00:19:36,290 --> 00:19:37,750
that my mom just missed me.

567
00:19:38,380 --> 00:19:40,640
That was the last time I talked to my mom.

568
00:19:42,170 --> 00:19:43,530
If my mom could see now

569
00:19:43,530 --> 00:19:44,730
that I can make money,

570
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:47,170
wouldn't she be very happy?

571
00:19:48,180 --> 00:19:49,310
She would.

572
00:19:49,310 --> 00:19:50,710
She definitely would be.

573
00:19:51,660 --> 00:19:53,530
Jun. When we get back,

574
00:19:53,530 --> 00:19:54,900
I'll treat you to Zhajiang noodles.

575
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:56,270
I'll treat you every day.

576
00:19:56,270 --> 00:19:58,010
No, let Liangliang do it.

577
00:19:58,800 --> 00:20:00,880
Let Liangliang make Zhajiang noodles
for me.

578
00:20:00,880 --> 00:20:02,180
By then, I'll throw money in his face

579
00:20:02,180 --> 00:20:02,460
and make him

580
00:20:02,460 --> 00:20:03,900
make Zhajiang noodles for me all night.

581
00:20:03,900 --> 00:20:05,500
I'll throw it in his face too.

582
00:20:09,310 --> 00:20:11,090
Come on, let's have a drink.

583
00:20:11,590 --> 00:20:12,050
Come on.

584
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:29,590
The garden is quiet late at night.

585
00:20:30,510 --> 00:20:35,550
Only the wind is singing softly.

586
00:20:36,140 --> 00:20:40,200
How beautiful the night is.

587
00:20:40,310 --> 00:20:43,920
It captivates my heart—

588
00:20:44,420 --> 00:20:49,960
the night in the suburbs of Moscow.

589
00:20:50,570 --> 00:20:54,200
How beautiful the night is.

590
00:20:54,680 --> 00:20:57,900
It captivates my heart—

591
00:20:58,440 --> 00:21:03,570
the night in the suburbs of Moscow.

592
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:16,800
Help me check your bag

593
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:19,000
and see if the things
we're bringing for your mom

594
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:19,790
are all there.

595
00:21:19,790 --> 00:21:21,850
Make sure we didn't forget anything.

596
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:22,380
Okay.

597
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:42,130
You bought this?

598
00:21:42,980 --> 00:21:43,780
Do you like it?

599
00:21:52,420 --> 00:21:53,370
Open it and see.

600
00:22:04,810 --> 00:22:07,010
Tao Liangliang, Shen Ranran.

601
00:22:05,850 --> 00:22:08,090
[Tao Liangliang] [Shen Ranran]

602
00:22:07,810 --> 00:22:09,140
I am your shell,

603
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:12,050
always protecting you.

604
00:22:19,310 --> 00:22:20,630
[Shen Ranran]

605
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:20,700
There's more?

606
00:22:22,830 --> 00:22:24,310
Why doesn't this one have a name?

607
00:22:24,310 --> 00:22:25,940
This is our child.

608
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:28,620
You can name it.

609
00:22:29,050 --> 00:22:30,850
What should we call it? Tao what?

610
00:22:31,700 --> 00:22:32,400
Tao Ranran.

611
00:22:32,750 --> 00:22:33,940
Tao Ranran?

612
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:35,570
Okay, good name.

613
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:37,660
There's a green one too?

614
00:22:37,660 --> 00:22:39,380
This is our second child.

615
00:22:42,830 --> 00:22:44,360
How many are there in total?

616
00:22:44,440 --> 00:22:45,770
This is our third child.

617
00:22:46,900 --> 00:22:47,680
One more?

618
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:50,300
This is our fourth.

619
00:22:50,420 --> 00:22:52,050
Didn't our parents' generation

620
00:22:52,050 --> 00:22:54,730
all have many children?

621
00:22:54,880 --> 00:22:55,960
There's more?

622
00:22:56,070 --> 00:22:56,610
Yeah.

623
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:01,850
How many do you want me to have?

624
00:23:16,110 --> 00:23:17,370
You bought this for me?

625
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:19,510
When I proposed before,

626
00:23:21,530 --> 00:23:22,460
I promised you

627
00:23:23,850 --> 00:23:25,180
I would make it up to you.

628
00:23:27,220 --> 00:23:28,220
What about yours?

629
00:23:29,240 --> 00:23:30,290
Mine...

630
00:23:31,250 --> 00:23:31,880
faded,

631
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,000
so I threw it away.

632
00:23:38,050 --> 00:23:41,250
Liangliang, do you think...

633
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:43,900
we will really

634
00:23:43,900 --> 00:23:45,310
be blessed by everyone?

635
00:23:50,660 --> 00:23:52,420
We didn't come into this world

636
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,480
for no reason.

637
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,570
After we met—

638
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:02,960
and in all the tomorrows to come—

639
00:24:04,590 --> 00:24:05,990
let's rely on each other.

640
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:10,200
Okay.

641
00:24:12,180 --> 00:24:12,660
Okay.

642
00:24:13,750 --> 00:24:14,850
Quick, put it on me.

643
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:35,000
Hello, Mrs. Shen.

644
00:24:35,380 --> 00:24:36,640
My name is Tao Liangliang.

645
00:24:36,640 --> 00:24:37,640
I'm from Beijing.

646
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:40,510
These are some

647
00:24:40,510 --> 00:24:42,180
local specialties from Beijing.

648
00:24:42,180 --> 00:24:43,710
I don't know your taste.

649
00:24:44,200 --> 00:24:46,220
If you like any of them,

650
00:24:46,500 --> 00:24:48,510
I will bring you more next time.

651
00:24:48,550 --> 00:24:49,080
And this.

652
00:24:49,270 --> 00:24:50,790
This is braised pork knuckle
that I asked my dad

653
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:51,830
to make specially for you.

654
00:24:51,830 --> 00:24:53,160
I've vacuum-sealed it.

655
00:25:00,980 --> 00:25:01,970
These

656
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:03,790
aren't to my taste.

657
00:25:09,550 --> 00:25:10,220
Mom.

658
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:18,160
Is there... anything you want to tell me?

659
00:25:19,220 --> 00:25:19,890
Mrs. Shen.

660
00:25:20,110 --> 00:25:21,160
We came here today

661
00:25:22,530 --> 00:25:24,240
to talk about us.

662
00:25:25,570 --> 00:25:26,810
About you two?

663
00:25:27,140 --> 00:25:28,200
What is it?

664
00:25:32,610 --> 00:25:33,790
Well, my grandpa

665
00:25:33,790 --> 00:25:35,190
left behind an old house.

666
00:25:35,900 --> 00:25:36,940
Then

667
00:25:37,380 --> 00:25:38,940
my parents renovated it

668
00:25:39,110 --> 00:25:40,640
and opened a small restaurant.

669
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:42,640
Lately, they've been talking about

670
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:44,070
remodeling the back area.

671
00:25:44,070 --> 00:25:46,380
They plan to live in the restaurant
in the future.

672
00:25:46,380 --> 00:25:48,000
And they'll leave the house

673
00:25:48,770 --> 00:25:50,300
they're living in now to us.

674
00:25:52,220 --> 00:25:54,280
For us to live in after we get married.

675
00:26:00,610 --> 00:26:01,210
This is...

676
00:26:01,610 --> 00:26:02,860
too ridiculous.

677
00:26:05,350 --> 00:26:06,610
After you get married?

678
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:08,480
Ranran,

679
00:26:08,790 --> 00:26:10,190
you are getting married?

680
00:26:12,010 --> 00:26:13,870
How can you afford to get married?

681
00:26:14,810 --> 00:26:16,110
Neither of you

682
00:26:16,640 --> 00:26:18,880
has a proper job.

683
00:26:19,010 --> 00:26:21,400
Where will you get the money to marry?

684
00:26:22,180 --> 00:26:23,050
How will you support a family?

685
00:26:23,050 --> 00:26:24,780
How will you raise children?

686
00:26:25,160 --> 00:26:26,180
Will you keep asking your parents

687
00:26:26,180 --> 00:26:27,510
for money in the future?

688
00:26:28,420 --> 00:26:28,900
Mom.

689
00:26:30,460 --> 00:26:31,880
We have jobs.

690
00:26:33,010 --> 00:26:33,870
Liangliang...

691
00:26:34,010 --> 00:26:35,290
Liangliang is very good at

692
00:26:35,290 --> 00:26:36,620
playing the saxophone.

693
00:26:36,640 --> 00:26:38,310
Many people hire him to perform.

694
00:26:38,310 --> 00:26:39,910
He makes thousands per show.

695
00:26:40,030 --> 00:26:41,290
He also does business.

696
00:26:41,720 --> 00:26:44,120
He goes to Russia for international trade.

697
00:26:44,140 --> 00:26:44,920
A single trip

698
00:26:44,920 --> 00:26:47,050
can earn him tens of thousands of yuan.

699
00:26:47,070 --> 00:26:49,570
In the future... the two of us...

700
00:26:50,790 --> 00:26:52,120
will work hard together

701
00:26:53,010 --> 00:26:54,070
and earn more money

702
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:56,430
to support you.

703
00:26:56,960 --> 00:26:57,350
Mrs. Shen,

704
00:26:57,350 --> 00:26:59,050
I will treat Ranran well.

705
00:27:01,030 --> 00:27:01,960
I will work hard.

706
00:27:03,070 --> 00:27:04,290
You will work hard?

707
00:27:04,940 --> 00:27:06,030
You are at this age

708
00:27:06,030 --> 00:27:08,030
and you haven't achieved anything.

709
00:27:08,300 --> 00:27:09,740
And you want to get married?

710
00:27:09,740 --> 00:27:11,050
Stop talking big.

711
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:13,260
Anyway, let me tell you,

712
00:27:13,750 --> 00:27:14,570
I won't agree

713
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:16,250
to your marriage.

714
00:27:18,900 --> 00:27:19,830
And Ranran,

715
00:27:19,960 --> 00:27:22,000
if you want to be with this poor boy,

716
00:27:22,720 --> 00:27:23,540
just do it.

717
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:25,720
In the future,

718
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:27,140
don't come to me again.

719
00:27:29,980 --> 00:27:31,570
I will never agree!

720
00:27:44,740 --> 00:27:45,320
Let's go.

721
00:27:46,200 --> 00:27:47,600
Let's go back to Beijing.

722
00:27:51,180 --> 00:27:53,140
You've bought everything you need.

723
00:27:53,140 --> 00:27:54,920
See if there's anything else
you want to take back.

724
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:56,330
We still have some time
before the train leaves.

725
00:27:56,330 --> 00:27:57,660
That's enough.

726
00:27:57,930 --> 00:27:59,260
When are you going back?

727
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:02,670
I am so busy here.

728
00:28:02,790 --> 00:28:04,270
I have to cooperate with you here

729
00:28:04,270 --> 00:28:05,200
and support you.

730
00:28:06,420 --> 00:28:07,150
That's true.

731
00:28:07,530 --> 00:28:09,730
And you can spend more time with Sophia.

732
00:28:09,830 --> 00:28:10,810
Why are you always joking?

733
00:28:10,810 --> 00:28:12,220
Stop joking.

734
00:28:12,250 --> 00:28:13,680
I have to do business here

735
00:28:13,700 --> 00:28:14,380
and cooperate with you.

736
00:28:14,380 --> 00:28:15,580
I need to support you.

737
00:28:15,750 --> 00:28:16,150
Right?

738
00:28:16,250 --> 00:28:16,920
Besides,

739
00:28:17,480 --> 00:28:18,550
Sophia and I...

740
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:21,060
Is it that obvious?

741
00:28:22,610 --> 00:28:23,870
What are brothers for?

742
00:28:24,700 --> 00:28:25,590
I can tell what you're thinking

743
00:28:25,590 --> 00:28:27,110
without you saying a word.

744
00:28:32,450 --> 00:28:33,920
Do you think she'll like me?

745
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:34,980
I can't really say.

746
00:28:36,220 --> 00:28:36,680
Yeah.

747
00:28:37,380 --> 00:28:38,240
I'm not young anymore.

748
00:28:38,240 --> 00:28:39,180
She's quite tall

749
00:28:39,480 --> 00:28:40,350
and better-looking than me.

750
00:28:40,350 --> 00:28:42,080
Then why did she help us so much?

751
00:28:43,290 --> 00:28:44,350
What does she want?

752
00:28:44,980 --> 00:28:45,440
Come on.

753
00:28:45,940 --> 00:28:47,110
You know,

754
00:28:47,240 --> 00:28:49,170
you're decisive in other matters.

755
00:28:49,240 --> 00:28:51,100
Why are you so hesitant with this?

756
00:28:56,060 --> 00:28:57,190
Me? Hesitant?

757
00:28:57,850 --> 00:28:59,780
It's because I didn't get a chance.

758
00:29:00,010 --> 00:29:01,740
If you give me a chance, I'll...

759
00:29:04,330 --> 00:29:04,990
Wait here.

760
00:29:09,810 --> 00:29:11,850
Flowers! Flowers!

761
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:20,700
Flowers! Flowers!

762
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:25,660
Kid, come here.

763
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:29,370
Flowers, sir?

764
00:29:29,570 --> 00:29:31,300
Which flower represents love?

765
00:29:31,420 --> 00:29:31,950
This one.

766
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:33,940
No red roses?

767
00:29:35,090 --> 00:29:36,820
You don't understand Chinese?

768
00:29:37,810 --> 00:29:38,380
Learn more Chinese,

769
00:29:38,380 --> 00:29:39,880
and you'll make a fortune in the future.

770
00:29:39,880 --> 00:29:40,610
Thank you.

771
00:29:40,610 --> 00:29:41,960
Thanks. Give me the change.

772
00:29:41,960 --> 00:29:42,960
Thank you.

773
00:29:43,200 --> 00:29:43,940
You don't understand this?

774
00:29:43,940 --> 00:29:45,750
Do you understand "give me the change"?

775
00:29:45,750 --> 00:29:46,110
Sir,

776
00:29:46,110 --> 00:29:47,350
please buy our flowers.

777
00:29:47,350 --> 00:29:49,040
So we'll be able to go home.

778
00:29:49,380 --> 00:29:50,510
I don't understand.

779
00:29:51,140 --> 00:29:52,090
Hurry up and go home.

780
00:29:52,090 --> 00:29:53,760
One bouquet is enough for me.

781
00:29:54,270 --> 00:29:54,920
I'll give you some money.

782
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:56,010
Take it as pocket money.

783
00:29:56,010 --> 00:29:57,020
Study hard.

784
00:30:04,090 --> 00:30:05,150
What are you doing?

785
00:30:05,770 --> 00:30:06,830
What are you doing?

786
00:31:05,940 --> 00:31:06,970
The attackers...

787
00:31:13,180 --> 00:31:15,110
The attackers have been caught.

788
00:31:15,980 --> 00:31:17,240
They're Sergey's men.

789
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:21,360
After the cremation ceremony tomorrow,

790
00:31:20,430 --> 00:31:26,220
[Death Certificate]

791
00:31:24,400 --> 00:31:25,810
you can take him home.

792
00:31:29,920 --> 00:31:31,420
He always liked to sit here

793
00:31:31,460 --> 00:31:32,610
and joke with us.

794
00:31:34,480 --> 00:31:35,420
This fool.

795
00:32:16,620 --> 00:32:20,220
♪ In one cold night of one year,
a dream took root ♪

796
00:32:22,330 --> 00:32:26,060
♪ One vow still holds a trace of warmth ♪

797
00:32:28,160 --> 00:32:32,740
♪ By one window, we once
sat together under a gentle light ♪

798
00:32:33,710 --> 00:32:38,300
♪ Yet in one turning,
we missed half a lifetime ♪

799
00:32:35,570 --> 00:32:36,650
-Jun.
-Jun.

800
00:32:36,670 --> 00:32:37,380
You flatter me.

801
00:32:37,380 --> 00:32:38,510
That's all in the past.

802
00:32:38,510 --> 00:32:39,830
Now I mainly do business.

803
00:32:39,830 --> 00:32:43,700
♪ One beam of light
scattered into the stars ♪

804
00:32:43,740 --> 00:32:45,480
The four of us will work together as one,

805
00:32:45,480 --> 00:32:46,920
charge forward, and make money!

806
00:32:46,180 --> 00:32:49,470
♪ In some emptiness,
I learned to be whole ♪

807
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:48,510
We will make a fortune!

808
00:32:48,720 --> 00:32:50,460
I have to keep you safe.

809
00:32:50,570 --> 00:32:52,610
We made it here safely.

810
00:32:51,750 --> 00:32:56,520
♪ At one station,
the sound of farewell became forever ♪

811
00:32:52,700 --> 00:32:54,400
We must leave in one piece too.

812
00:32:54,420 --> 00:32:55,590
Be careful in everything you do.

813
00:32:55,590 --> 00:32:56,480
You have to listen to me.

814
00:32:56,480 --> 00:32:57,510
Do you understand?

815
00:32:57,510 --> 00:33:02,110
♪ Some journey has no way back ♪

816
00:33:01,110 --> 00:33:02,350
I still hadn't figured out

817
00:33:02,350 --> 00:33:03,950
what kind of person you were.

818
00:33:04,140 --> 00:33:05,770
Now you know what kind of person I am?

819
00:33:05,770 --> 00:33:07,220
You have many good qualities.

820
00:33:05,920 --> 00:33:10,380
♪ In one winter,
my hands were no longer cold ♪

821
00:33:07,810 --> 00:33:09,670
Just as many as the bad ones I have.

822
00:33:10,510 --> 00:33:11,460
Trust Lucky Ma,

823
00:33:11,340 --> 00:33:16,410
♪ My path ahead is carved into
every line of my palms ♪

824
00:33:11,460 --> 00:33:13,570
work with Lucky Ma,
and good luck will find you!

825
00:33:13,570 --> 00:33:15,180
We're actually very suited
for doing business.

826
00:33:15,180 --> 00:33:16,740
Look, you have a strong physique,

827
00:33:16,740 --> 00:33:17,660
and I have a smart brain.

828
00:33:17,550 --> 00:33:22,250
♪ One spring,
I opened the envelope of the past ♪

829
00:33:17,680 --> 00:33:18,880
Let's shout a slogan.

830
00:33:18,880 --> 00:33:19,720
It's called,

831
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:20,810
"Life is about striving."

832
00:33:20,810 --> 00:33:21,140
I'll shout 'life'.

833
00:33:21,140 --> 00:33:21,680
And you shout "is about striving."

834
00:33:21,680 --> 00:33:22,290
-Okay.
-Okay!

835
00:33:22,290 --> 00:33:22,980
Life!

836
00:33:22,980 --> 00:33:25,160
Is about striving!

837
00:33:23,230 --> 00:33:30,930
♪ The answers were already
written on every page of life ♪

838
00:33:37,940 --> 00:33:39,290
If you walk out today,

839
00:33:40,140 --> 00:33:41,970
we're done!

840
00:33:42,030 --> 00:33:43,030
Fine, we're done.

841
00:33:45,060 --> 00:33:47,990
Even if you die out there,
it has nothing to do with me!

842
00:33:52,310 --> 00:33:53,720
You invested more and earned more,

843
00:33:53,720 --> 00:33:55,010
and you can buy a car later.

844
00:33:55,010 --> 00:33:56,220
You invested little and earned little,

845
00:33:55,830 --> 00:33:58,720
♪ Enduring forever ♪

846
00:33:56,540 --> 00:33:58,270
I still gave you a higher total.

847
00:34:14,960 --> 00:34:16,889
Is everything about Jun arranged?

848
00:34:24,780 --> 00:34:25,440
Recently,

849
00:34:25,460 --> 00:34:28,320
Liangliang has been
keeping Jun's father company.

850
00:34:31,190 --> 00:34:32,090
The place

851
00:34:32,090 --> 00:34:33,440
we chose for Jun...

852
00:34:35,300 --> 00:34:36,400
is quite spacious.

853
00:34:37,320 --> 00:34:38,850
He will definitely like it.

854
00:34:45,210 --> 00:34:46,440
Last time we came here,

855
00:34:46,440 --> 00:34:48,100
we were talking about movies.

856
00:34:50,070 --> 00:34:52,000
It seems that in the blink of an eye,

857
00:34:52,340 --> 00:34:54,350
our lives

858
00:34:55,530 --> 00:34:56,460
have

859
00:34:58,700 --> 00:34:59,580
taken a turn

860
00:34:59,610 --> 00:35:00,670
we never imagined.

861
00:35:02,570 --> 00:35:03,370
It's like life

862
00:35:03,400 --> 00:35:05,110
was suddenly put on pause,

863
00:35:06,150 --> 00:35:07,560
forcing us to stop

864
00:35:07,590 --> 00:35:09,790
and think carefully about many things.

865
00:35:11,810 --> 00:35:13,120
While my mom was sick,

866
00:35:13,150 --> 00:35:14,350
I did a lot of thinking

867
00:35:14,980 --> 00:35:16,580
and gave up the competition.

868
00:35:22,960 --> 00:35:23,840
Lately,

869
00:35:25,140 --> 00:35:27,280
I often think about

870
00:35:27,850 --> 00:35:28,370
the days

871
00:35:28,400 --> 00:35:30,200
we chased our dreams in Beijing.

872
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:32,180
We laughed, and we cried.

873
00:35:33,550 --> 00:35:35,280
Every face was so bright.

874
00:35:38,860 --> 00:35:39,670
Sometimes

875
00:35:39,690 --> 00:35:41,620
we did run into some difficulties,

876
00:35:41,650 --> 00:35:43,110
but being together

877
00:35:43,940 --> 00:35:44,530
made it

878
00:35:44,550 --> 00:35:45,800
not feel so bad.

879
00:35:51,280 --> 00:35:52,140
Thank you.

880
00:35:52,960 --> 00:35:55,220
For bringing me to Seasons Change Hostel

881
00:35:55,360 --> 00:35:56,190
and letting me feel

882
00:35:56,190 --> 00:35:57,110
so much warmth.

883
00:35:58,260 --> 00:36:00,060
I should be the one thanking you.

884
00:36:01,090 --> 00:36:02,960
You gave me a lot of warmth.

885
00:36:09,250 --> 00:36:10,250
I'm done singing.

886
00:36:15,510 --> 00:36:17,260
Singing does make me happy,

887
00:36:18,080 --> 00:36:19,350
but I've realized

888
00:36:20,150 --> 00:36:21,750
that passion and profession

889
00:36:22,360 --> 00:36:23,620
can't always coexist.

890
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:27,610
Sometimes, chasing too hard

891
00:36:29,070 --> 00:36:29,980
can actually drain

892
00:36:29,980 --> 00:36:30,910
your love for it.

893
00:36:34,690 --> 00:36:36,010
So now I want to try

894
00:36:36,030 --> 00:36:37,970
designing clothes.

895
00:36:38,230 --> 00:36:39,370
Back at Ruhua,

896
00:36:39,900 --> 00:36:41,720
I found I actually

897
00:36:41,780 --> 00:36:42,980
quite like it.

898
00:36:44,730 --> 00:36:45,790
I'll give it a shot.

899
00:36:46,190 --> 00:36:47,990
Maybe this path suits me better.

900
00:36:49,800 --> 00:36:50,840
You are right.

901
00:36:52,550 --> 00:36:55,070
Few people manage to turn their passion

902
00:36:55,090 --> 00:36:56,190
into a career.

903
00:36:57,030 --> 00:36:58,690
I've also thought it through.

904
00:36:59,440 --> 00:37:02,300
Writing is still my passion.

905
00:37:03,650 --> 00:37:05,390
So I'll just keep it

906
00:37:05,610 --> 00:37:07,720
as something that's always ongoing.

907
00:37:09,570 --> 00:37:11,460
During my time in Russia,

908
00:37:12,360 --> 00:37:13,400
I thought a lot.

909
00:37:15,260 --> 00:37:17,390
I realized that doing business

910
00:37:19,620 --> 00:37:21,680
also brings me a lot of satisfaction.

911
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:23,470
Didn't you just say

912
00:37:23,500 --> 00:37:24,960
you want to try designing?

913
00:37:25,590 --> 00:37:28,120
Then I'll help you
to sell your clothes later.

914
00:37:30,900 --> 00:37:33,290
Maybe our previous dreams

915
00:37:34,760 --> 00:37:36,160
just lacked a bit of luck.

916
00:37:36,530 --> 00:37:37,790
But it doesn't matter.

917
00:37:38,610 --> 00:37:39,800
Now we can say

918
00:37:39,800 --> 00:37:41,060
we have a shared dream.

919
00:37:43,340 --> 00:37:44,090
I used to think

920
00:37:44,090 --> 00:37:45,900
dreams were the most important thing.

921
00:37:45,900 --> 00:37:46,920
But now I feel

922
00:37:47,980 --> 00:37:50,180
the person who can chase dreams with you

923
00:37:50,710 --> 00:37:51,970
is the most important.

924
00:38:02,630 --> 00:38:03,860
No matter which path

925
00:38:05,110 --> 00:38:06,640
life takes us in the future,

926
00:38:10,360 --> 00:38:11,000
I hope I can

927
00:38:11,010 --> 00:38:12,190
hold your hand

928
00:38:15,860 --> 00:38:17,390
and keep walking together.

929
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:42,030
Are you really getting married,

930
00:38:42,030 --> 00:38:42,930
Ranran?

931
00:38:43,210 --> 00:38:44,010
Yes.

932
00:38:44,030 --> 00:38:45,000
I'd like to invite you

933
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:46,550
and your parents to come to the wedding.

934
00:38:46,550 --> 00:38:48,080
I miss you so much.

935
00:38:48,340 --> 00:38:49,470
That's great.

936
00:38:49,710 --> 00:38:50,860
I can live in the Seasons Change Hostel

937
00:38:50,860 --> 00:38:52,330
with everyone again.

938
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:53,010
Oh, no.

939
00:38:53,590 --> 00:38:54,170
This kid,

940
00:38:54,190 --> 00:38:56,220
you were influenced by Liangliang.

941
00:38:56,260 --> 00:38:57,230
You're just a kid,

942
00:38:57,230 --> 00:38:59,560
and you don't want
to live at home anymore.

943
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:00,520
Ranran,

944
00:39:00,630 --> 00:39:03,260
your aunt wants to talk to you.

945
00:39:03,920 --> 00:39:04,380
Okay.

946
00:39:04,980 --> 00:39:05,580
Go ahead.

947
00:39:07,530 --> 00:39:08,760
Ranran.

948
00:39:09,340 --> 00:39:11,410
Farming has been busy recently,

949
00:39:11,690 --> 00:39:13,090
so I might not be able

950
00:39:13,130 --> 00:39:15,290
to attend your wedding.

951
00:39:15,820 --> 00:39:17,380
I'll have Xiaobao

952
00:39:17,420 --> 00:39:19,970
bring my gift to you.

953
00:39:21,210 --> 00:39:25,460
I wish you a happy marriage

954
00:39:26,300 --> 00:39:28,710
and a long life together.

955
00:39:29,170 --> 00:39:30,160
Great.

956
00:39:30,230 --> 00:39:31,480
Well said.

957
00:39:32,180 --> 00:39:33,700
Have a baby soon!

958
00:39:34,120 --> 00:39:35,320
Have a baby soon!

959
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:38,670
Have a baby soon!

960
00:39:38,900 --> 00:39:40,210
Thank you, Mrs. Guo.

961
00:39:41,280 --> 00:39:42,650
When I'm free,

962
00:39:42,860 --> 00:39:43,550
I'll go to Henan specifically

963
00:39:43,550 --> 00:39:44,880
to visit you.

964
00:39:46,050 --> 00:39:47,440
You're welcome.

965
00:39:48,090 --> 00:39:48,730
Okay!

966
00:39:49,710 --> 00:39:51,010
I'll hang up now.

967
00:39:54,940 --> 00:39:56,230
She can speak now?

968
00:39:56,900 --> 00:39:58,810
She said quite a lot.

969
00:40:01,760 --> 00:40:02,710
Everyone at the Seasons Change Hostel

970
00:40:02,710 --> 00:40:03,970
is bringing good news.

971
00:40:03,980 --> 00:40:07,000
Shengli and Zhuang Zhuang
have also returned to Beijing.

972
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:08,010
I'll go tidy up the room.

973
00:40:08,010 --> 00:40:09,650
Really? I'll go with you.

974
00:40:09,760 --> 00:40:10,650
Let's go then.

975
00:40:11,840 --> 00:40:12,300
Come on.

976
00:40:14,820 --> 00:40:15,980
So beautiful.

977
00:40:17,210 --> 00:40:18,360
You're the most beautiful bride.

978
00:40:18,360 --> 00:40:19,360
This is the most beautiful dress

979
00:40:19,360 --> 00:40:20,620
I have ever worn.

980
00:40:20,730 --> 00:40:21,440
Really?

981
00:40:22,650 --> 00:40:24,150
You've been so busy lately,

982
00:40:24,150 --> 00:40:25,940
yet you still made this outfit for me.

983
00:40:25,940 --> 00:40:27,470
What are you talking about?

984
00:40:27,590 --> 00:40:28,780
For such an important day,

985
00:40:28,780 --> 00:40:30,200
I had to make it for you.

986
00:40:35,760 --> 00:40:36,760
From now on,

987
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:38,280
I won't be around you,

988
00:40:39,230 --> 00:40:41,050
but you still need to look pretty.

989
00:40:41,050 --> 00:40:42,770
Most importantly, be happy.

990
00:40:43,090 --> 00:40:43,940
Of course.

991
00:40:45,190 --> 00:40:46,440
Zhuang, come with me.

992
00:40:49,070 --> 00:40:49,600
Sit here.

993
00:40:54,820 --> 00:40:55,680
This is for you.

994
00:40:56,610 --> 00:40:57,380
For me?

995
00:41:03,150 --> 00:41:04,440
I was afraid I wouldn't be there

996
00:41:04,440 --> 00:41:05,590
for your important moments,

997
00:41:05,590 --> 00:41:06,510
so I bought this

998
00:41:06,550 --> 00:41:08,940
little golden lock
for your future baby in advance.

999
00:41:08,940 --> 00:41:10,600
You bought this way too early.

1000
00:41:11,190 --> 00:41:11,920
No, I didn't.

1001
00:41:15,570 --> 00:41:16,340
You

1002
00:41:16,780 --> 00:41:18,500
spent all your money on us.

1003
00:41:19,430 --> 00:41:20,540
You sound

1004
00:41:20,570 --> 00:41:22,090
like a matriarch.

1005
00:41:23,880 --> 00:41:24,480
I love it.

1006
00:41:28,420 --> 00:41:30,650
You just said
you wouldn't be here anymore?

1007
00:41:30,650 --> 00:41:31,780
Where are you going?

1008
00:41:31,900 --> 00:41:34,040
Isn't going abroad popular now?

1009
00:41:34,130 --> 00:41:35,840
While you were away,

1010
00:41:36,070 --> 00:41:37,300
I took foreign language classes

1011
00:41:37,300 --> 00:41:38,430
and learned French.

1012
00:41:38,670 --> 00:41:39,720
French?

1013
00:41:40,030 --> 00:41:41,280
Are you going to France?

1014
00:41:41,280 --> 00:41:41,980
Yes.

1015
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:44,010
That's the capital of fashion.

1016
00:41:44,500 --> 00:41:45,780
I have a classmate in France

1017
00:41:45,780 --> 00:41:48,060
who runs a group tour business

1018
00:41:48,090 --> 00:41:50,150
specifically for Chinese tourists.

1019
00:41:50,300 --> 00:41:50,590
I think

1020
00:41:50,590 --> 00:41:51,710
it's a great opportunity.

1021
00:41:51,710 --> 00:41:53,110
And I want to give it a try.

1022
00:41:53,550 --> 00:41:55,820
Mr. Guo just paid me back.

1023
00:41:56,150 --> 00:41:57,320
And Liangliang's parents

1024
00:41:57,320 --> 00:41:58,780
are very supportive of us.

1025
00:41:58,880 --> 00:41:59,410
They said

1026
00:41:59,440 --> 00:42:00,420
young people should

1027
00:42:00,420 --> 00:42:02,150
go out and seek their fortunes.

1028
00:42:02,210 --> 00:42:03,630
Once my French is good enough,

1029
00:42:03,630 --> 00:42:05,090
we'll go to France.

1030
00:42:06,070 --> 00:42:06,870
That's great.

1031
00:42:07,880 --> 00:42:09,010
But it's so far away.

1032
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:10,600
Will you two be okay?

1033
00:42:11,070 --> 00:42:13,930
We've been through so much together.

1034
00:42:14,150 --> 00:42:16,740
We're indestructible warriors.

1035
00:42:17,670 --> 00:42:19,860
It's just that French is too hard.

1036
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:22,310
"Hello."

1037
00:42:22,610 --> 00:42:24,110
"I'm doing well too."

1038
00:42:28,380 --> 00:42:29,360
When you first got here,

1039
00:42:29,360 --> 00:42:31,160
you were like a little hedgehog.

1040
00:42:31,400 --> 00:42:34,130
Now you're getting married
in the blink of an eye.

1041
00:42:34,730 --> 00:42:36,410
Zhuang, why are you crying?

1042
00:42:36,900 --> 00:42:37,740
I'll miss you.

1043
00:42:40,550 --> 00:42:42,880
For the past 2 years
at the Seasons Change Hostel,

1044
00:42:42,880 --> 00:42:43,530
thank you.

1045
00:42:44,340 --> 00:42:45,270
No need for that.

1046
00:42:48,860 --> 00:42:49,580
Alright.

1047
00:42:52,440 --> 00:42:52,920
That's great.
